esssim 100L_{\\rm Edd}/c^2$. Our simulations also reveal\nthat the gas temperature in the overheated regions depends on black hole spin,\nwhich would be due to efficient energy transport from black hole to disks\nthrough the Poynting flux, resulting gas heating.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 May 2016 01:14:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-07-27"}
