ere is a critical end point of second-order\nstructural transition at $x = 0.5$, where spin fluctuations become critically\nsingular and follow the exact scaling of conformally invariant boundary field\ntheory. The critical end point of quasi-$3D$ nature is associated with an\neffective dimensional cross-over between the $x = 2.0$ and $x=0.0$ quasi-$2D$\nstructures. Finally we draw a modified magnetic phase diagram of the material,\nshowing a fan-like region starting from the quantum critical end point at $x =\n0.5.$\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 May 2016 15:43:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-10"}
