{"id":"1606.06963","submitter":"Farida Tahir","authors":"O. F. Akinto, Farida Tahir","title":"Strong Gravity Approach to QCD and General Relativity","comments":"Modified Version of, \"Strong Gravity Approach to QCD and General\n  Relativity\"","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"physics.gen-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  A systematic study of the Weyl-type / Yang-Mills-type action possessing local\nconformal invariance and quadratic curvature is undertaken. The dynamical\nbreaking of this conformal invariance / scale invariance induces general\nrelativity (GR) as an effective long distance limit of the theory. We prove\nthat the corresponding field equations of the theory have the linearly rising\npotential, which naturally possesses asymptotic freedom and color confinement\nproperties of quantum chromodynamics (QCD). Solutions to the neutrino mass and\ndark energy problems come as free gifts of this formulation. This approach\nprovides a strong gravity basis for the unification of quantum Yang-Mills\ntheory (QYMT) with Einstein GR.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 May 2016 09:31:45 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 15 Aug 2016 12:51:13 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 31 Aug 2016 08:45:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-01"}
